<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I wrote once <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/30494731.273449/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9=
vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDEtMDUvY29pbmRlYWwtcy1iZW50bGV5cy13ZXJlbi10LX=
JlYWw_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDIwODIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291c=
mNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwMjA4JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607=
f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2bebb511" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsco=
pe" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impor=
tant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom=
-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> about the crime dial</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In general, the chief compliance o=
fficer at any company has a dial in front of her that she can turn to get M=
ore Crime or Less Crime, and at a normal company =E2=80=94 a bank, for inst=
ance =E2=80=94 her job consists of (1) turning it most of the way toward Le=
ss Crime, but (2) not all the way, and (3) acting very contrite when politi=
cians and regulators yell at her about the residual crime. =E2=80=9CWe have=
 a zero-tolerance policy for crime,=E2=80=9D she will say, and almost mean.=
</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Now, in practice, every day, a bank=E2=80=99s =
compliance officer will face the choice of (1) leaving the dial alone, (2) =
turning it a touch toward More Crime or (3) turning it a touch toward Less =
Crime. Presumably most days she will mostly leave it alone and focus on oth=
er things. Some days, she will adjust it a scooch one way or the other, in =
ways that don=E2=80=99t really get noticed much outside of the bank. Occasi=
onally the dial will have drifted too far toward More Crime, the bank will =
have a huge scandal, she will be fired, and her successor will make a big s=
how of cranking the dial a long way toward Less Crime. =E2=80=9CWe had too =
much crime,=E2=80=9D the new compliance officer will say, =E2=80=9Cbut from=
 now on we will have a zero-tolerance policy toward crime.=E2=80=9D This st=
ill won=E2=80=99t be true, but it will (1) still almost be true and (2) be =
a bit more true than it was before the scandal.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This problem is not wholly symmetrical: It is =
rarer for the bank to run into huge problems because the dial has drifted t=
oo far toward Less Crime, and to then make a big show of cranking the dial =
a long way toward More Crime. =E2=80=9CWe had too little crime,=E2=80=9D a =
bank=E2=80=99s compliance officer will pretty much never say, =E2=80=9Cbut =
from now on we will have a much more tolerant policy toward crime.=E2=80=9D=
</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Still! The problem is a <em>little=C2=A0</em>s=
ymmetrical.=C2=A0One way to ensure that you never do any illegal business i=
s to never do any business,<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-6"=
 style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-w=
idth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !importa=
nt; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[6]</span>
</a> and that probably goes too far. Sometimes you do have to <a href=3D"ht=
tps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30494731.273449/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3c=
uYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDItMDgvY3JlZGl0LXN1aXNzZS1kaW=
Fscy1iYWNrLWFzaWEtcmlzay1jb250cm9scy1hZnRlci1iYW5rZXJzLXJldm9sdD9jbXBpZD1CQ=
kQwMjA4MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRl=
ciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzAyMDgmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cB9f60e325" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_b=
lank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;"> crank the dial back</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Credit Suisse Group AG, fighting to stem a wav=
e of investor outflows, is dialing back some stringent anti-money launderin=
g controls in Asia after they drew protests from clients and bankers and co=
ntributed to staff departures.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A requirement that private bankers verify most=
 of their clients=E2=80=99 sources of wealth was eased near the end of last=
 year, while third-party transactions are no longer subject to executive ap=
provals, according to people familiar with the matter.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The backtracking highlights the delicate balan=
ce facing the bank as it tries to tighten operations following a series of =
scandals, while hanging on to clients in one of the fastest-growing regions=
 for money management. The measures, more stringent than at many peers, thr=
eatened to stall efforts to recover from massive outflows that contributed =
to another quarterly loss for the embattled bank.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One funny part of this story is that, after Cr=
edit Suisse had various scandals, it =E2=80=9Ctook steps in 2021 to tighten=
 controls by commissioning Ernst &amp; Young to assess its wealth units=E2=
=80=99 anti-money laundering procedures in Singapore and Hong Kong.=E2=80=
=9D If you are an outside auditor brought in to do a report on anti-money l=
aundering procedures, the problem is not symmetrical at all,=C2=A0<em>for y=
ou</em>. If you recommend =E2=80=9Ca robust =E2=80=98belt and braces=E2=80=
=99 approach=E2=80=9D (as a Credit Suisse spokesperson called it in a state=
ment to Bloomberg News), and the approach is=C2=A0<em>so=C2=A0</em>robust t=
hat the clients can never get business approved and the bankers all quit, t=
hat=E2=80=99s not=C2=A0<em>your=C2=A0</em>problem; you were hired to stop m=
oney laundering, and you did. You bring in an outside consultant, you=E2=80=
=99re gonna get the dial cranked way too far over toward Less Crime. And th=
en you have to nudge it back.</p>
