<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One thing that you can do is make a handbag th=
at looks like an Herm=C3=A8s Birkin bag, call it a =E2=80=9CBirkin bag,=E2=
=80=9D and sell it to people for money. The problems with this are:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Hard to make the bag, you need materi=
als and labor and stuff, you=E2=80=99ve got to ship it to customers, etc.; =
and</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You are definitely violating H=
erm=C3=A8s=E2=80=99s trademark and they=E2=80=99ll sue you and win.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Another thing you can do is draw a picture on =
your computer that looks like an Herm=C3=A8s Birkin bag, call it (the pictu=
re) a =E2=80=9CMetaBirkin bag,=E2=80=9D and sell it to people for money. Th=
e advantages of this are:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Pretty easy to draw a picture on your=
 computer, and your shipping costs (of emailing people the picture) are neg=
ligible.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If Herm=C3=A8s sues you, =
you can do a dumb little dance and say =E2=80=9Cwhat, no, I=E2=80=99m not=
=C2=A0<em>copying=C2=A0</em>your=C2=A0<em>Birkin bag</em>, I am making a sl=
y and subtle joke about value and consumption and late capitalism.=E2=80=9D=
</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You might naively think that people would=C2=
=A0<em>pay less money=C2=A0</em>for a computer picture of a handbag than th=
ey would for an actual handbag, but in the early 2020s there was a brief bi=
zarre bubble in non-fungible tokens, and for a while people would pay=C2=A0=
<em>more=C2=A0</em>for a computer picture of a thing than for the actual th=
ing. There<em> were</em> some good jokes to be made about value and consump=
tion and late capitalism, but Herm=C3=A8s was not really the problem.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway this happened,=C2=A0Herm=C3=A8s did sue=
 the MetaBirkin guy, we <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/=
click/30494731.273449/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljb=
GVzLzIwMjMtMDEtMzAvaWJ1eWVycy1ib3VnaHQtaGlnaC1hbmQtc29sZC1sb3c_Y21waWQ9QkJE=
MDIwODIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXI=
mdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwMjA4JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a=
23cB87bf0643" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bla=
nk" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; bac=
kground-color: #ccc;">talked about it the other day</a>, and <a href=3D"htt=
ps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30494731.273449/aHR0cHM6Ly9uZXdz=
LmJsb29tYmVyZ2xhdy5jb20vaXAtbGF3L2hlcm1lcy1nZXRzLXdpbi1vdmVyLW1ldGFiaXJraW5=
zLWluLWZpcnN0LW5mdC10cmFkZW1hcmstdHJpYWw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB4eac5eae"=
 itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color=
: #ccc;">today Herm=C3=A8s won</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Luxury brand Herm=C3=A8s International SA won =
its lawsuit against the digital artist behind =E2=80=9CMetaBirkin=E2=80=9D =
nonfungible tokens after convincing a Manhattan federal jury that Mason Rot=
hschild=E2=80=99s sale of the NFTs violated Herm=C3=A8s=E2=80=99 rights to =
the =E2=80=9CBirkin=E2=80=9D trademark.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The nine-person jury returned a verdict on Wed=
nesday, awarding Herm=C3=A8s $133,000 in total damages. They also found Rot=
hschild=E2=80=99s NFTs aren=E2=80=99t protected speech under the First Amen=
dment. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The 100 MetaBirkin NFTs are linked to digital =
images depicting Herm=C3=A8s=E2=80=99 iconic Birkin luxury handbag, but cov=
ered in colorful, cartoonish fur instead of leather. Rothschild created and=
 sold the NFTs in late 2021 after an extensive marketing campaign through h=
is social media and website.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The jury determined that the NFTs are more aki=
n to consumer products subject to strict trademark laws that protect brands=
 from copycats and those looking to capitalize on their goodwill.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Throughout the case, Rothschild argued that hi=
s NFTs are works of art protected by the First Amendment, no different from=
 Andy Warhol=E2=80=99s famous silk-screen prints of Campbell=E2=80=99s soup=
 cans. His attorneys characterized the NFT project as an =E2=80=9Cartistic =
experiment=E2=80=9D that examined how society places value on status symbol=
s.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Physical Birkin bags range in price from $12,0=
00 to close to $200,000. Rothschild first sold the NFTs for around $450 eac=
h, but their resale value rocketed to tens of thousands of dollars.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A blockchain expert testified during trial tha=
t Rothschild made around 55.2 Ethereum tokens, worth about $87,700 today.</=
p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Look, do you know what is a good =E2=80=9Carti=
stic experiment that examines how society places value on status symbols=E2=
=80=9D?=C2=A0<em>Herm=C3=A8s</em>. Herm=C3=A8s is running a constant sophis=
ticated experiment in how society places value on status symbols: It produc=
es=C2=A0status symbols, tries to price them to extract maximum value, tries=
 to balance=C2=A0exclusivity against maximizing revenue, etc. You don=E2=80=
=99t need some computer guy to come along and be like =E2=80=9Cooooh ooooh =
ooooh these handbags sell at a premium to their cost of production, what is=
 society even doing,=C2=A0ooooh,=C2=A0ooooh.=E2=80=9D Herm=C3=A8s does that=
! That=E2=80=99s Herm=C3=A8s=E2=80=99s whole business!=C2=A0<em>They=E2=80=
=99re=C2=A0</em>not confused about what they=E2=80=99re doing! The people w=
ho buy Birkin bags aren=E2=80=99t confused about what they=E2=80=99re doing=
! Rothschild didn=E2=80=99t need to clarify or examine it! Herm=C3=A8s is d=
oing it fine!</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Obviously Rothschild=E2=80=99s experiment inst=
ead examined how society placed value on <em>computer images that imitate B=
irkin bags</em>, and for a while the answer was =E2=80=9Csociety values tho=
se pictures a lot because they are somehow status symbols.=E2=80=9D In some=
 sense anyone who does any scam is running an artistic experiment that exam=
ines how much money people are willing to give them, but that is not a defe=
nse!</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I guess the next step is to seize the MetaBirk=
ins and shred them? In the metaverse or whatever? And take a video of the s=
hredding and sell that as an NFT? Man what an embarrassing time the NFT boo=
m was.</p>
